The article discusses the first day of the Summit for Democracy, a virtual event hosted by President Biden. The summit aims to bring together leaders, lawmakers, and civil society leaders from around the world to discuss democratic resilience, tackling corruption, and building back better from the COVID-19 pandemic. The summit highlights the importance of sub-national and non-governmental actors in the democratic process. President Biden announced the Presidential Initiative for Democratic Renewal, which includes policy and foreign assistance initiatives to defend and bolster democracy, human rights, and the fight against corruption globally. The initiative focuses on supporting free and independent media, fighting corruption, bolstering democratic reformers, advancing technology for democracy, and defending free and fair election processes. Specific initiatives include supporting and protecting journalists, strengthening anti-corruption efforts, and promoting electoral integrity. The article also mentions that the summit does not specifically target any one country, and there is no outcome document expected at the end of the summit.